An internal link to [start](start) and one to a
[page](/some/namespace/page) target.

A named internal link to [the start page](start) guides the reader.

External links such as [Example](https://example.com) and the bare form
<https://example.org> both work, as does an email like
<user@example.com>.

An interwiki shortcut points at
[Wiki](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiki) for background reading.
